# Solana — project context

## Frontend (`frontend/index.html`, Babel in browser)

- All **user-facing strings in Spanish**. Add keys to the existing **`TR`** object; same pattern as current translations.
- **Do not** refactor into Vite/modules or change the build: edits stay inside the existing **`<script type="text/babel">`** block (~4k lines).

## Brand (new UI)

- Primary `#3C0A37`, accent `#C4622D`, badge `#7A4F9A`, background `#F5F0EA`.

## Auth (do not change model)

- **`ADMIN_KEY`**: shared secret for the pending-approvals admin panel — **not** per-user.
- **Session tokens**: HMAC-signed (not JWT), payload `{ userId, role, exp }`. Do not switch to JWT.
- **`requireAuth`**: same idea as `requireAuth` / `requireAdminSession` in `server.js` — validate Bearer token, set **`req.userId`** and **`req.userRole`**. For “any logged-in role”, accept any valid session (not only admin).

## Server / data

- **Render disk**: `/opt/render/project/src/data` — SQLite DB, backups, receipts.
- **Receipts**: `data/receipts/` on that disk; filename keyed by **expense id** (as today).
- **`seed.js` / bootstrap endpoints**: keep working with SQLite; disaster recovery only.
- **Errors**: Spanish, match existing phrases (`No autorizado.`, `Datos incompletos.`, `Usuario no encontrado.`, etc.).

## Security

- **Ownership on every expense/bill mutating route**: caller **owns** the resource **or** is **admin/superadmin**. Never rely on the client alone.

## Offline queue (`frontend`)

- **localStorage** key **`solana_offline_queue`**: array of `{ method, path, body, meta?, … }`; replay **FIFO** (see existing `API.flushOfflineQueue`).

## Currency

- Default **EUR**. **`amountEUR`**: for reporting; if currency is EUR then `amountEUR = amount`; if non-EUR, user enters EUR equivalent in the UI (**no** live FX API in v1).

## Cursor workspace

- Rule globs use `solana/**/*` when the repo lives under a parent folder (e.g. Desktop). If you open **`solana` as the workspace root**, edit this file’s frontmatter to `globs: **/*` or `alwaysApply: true`.
